Look.

The look command describes your current room.

When screenreader support is on, look uses a conversational room summary. It
tells you where you are, gives the first sentence of the room description, lists
the exits, then lists visible NPCs, visible players, and visible items.

Common forms:

look
  Describe the room.

l
  Short alias for look.

look <thing>
  Look directly at a named person, creature, item, or room detail.

actions
  List room-specific actions, things to look at, and things to read.

exa <thing>
examine <thing>
  Other ways to look closely at something.

If the room is dark or you are blind, look may not be able to describe your
surroundings.
